<h2 id="introduction">Introduction</h2>

<p>The problem comes from a stochastic PDE:</p>

\[\dfrac{du}{dt}=\Delta u-Eu^2+\xi\]

<p>Where Â  $u$ Â  is a function of $t$ and $x$, $x\in$ [0,1], and Â  $\xi$ Â  is space-time white noise.</p>

<p>We want to understand invariant measure of the stochastic PDE.</p>

<p>However, since itâ€™s complicated to deal with SPDE, we can try to make a finite difference approximation. Letâ€™s take n points from [0,1].</p>

<p>Then it becomes an SDE system:</p>

\[dX_i=(X_{i-1}+X_{i+1}-2X_{i}-EX_i^2\cdot X_i)dt+dB_i\]

